# React Components

## Before creating a component

1. Check `src/components/` for an existing component that can be extended.
2. Define purpose, props, and whether it must be a Client or Server Component.
3. Match patterns from `MovieCard`, `MovieGrid`, `PosterImage`, and `SearchBar`.

## Server vs client

- Default to Server Components (no `"use client"`).
- Add `"use client"` only when using `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, or `next/navigation` client hooks (`useRouter`, `useSearchParams`).

## Props and types

- Export a named function component with typed props.
- Import shared types from `@/types/` (e.g. `Movie`).
- Keep presentation components pure; pass data and callbacks via props.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes; follow the zinc/amber theme used elsewhere.
- Ensure interactive elements have accessible labels (`aria-label`, visible text, or `alt` on images).

## Images

- Use `next/image` in `PosterImage` and similar components.
- Provide meaningful `alt` text derived from movie title or context.

## Imports

- Use path alias `@/components/...` and `@/types/...`.
- Do not introduce shadcn/ui or external component libraries unless explicitly requested.

## Tests

- Add a colocated `ComponentName.test.tsx` using Vitest and Testing Library.
- Test rendered output and user-visible behavior, not implementation details.
